Go to AWS;

Select the server instance;

Click in "Actions";

Click in "Networking";

Click in "Change source/destination check";

Click in"Stop";

Click in "Save";



-> yum install iptables-services -y


-> systemctl enable --now iptables


-> iptables -F && iptables -t nat -A POSTROUTING -o eth0 -j MASQUERADE && netfilter-persistent save


-> nano /etc/sysctl.d/99-sysctl.conf && sysctl -p
#Add this line: "net.ipv4.ip_forward = 1"


####################
#IP Tables commands#
####################

Redirect any incoming traffic on port 80 or 443 into your server IP to another machine in the same network.

-> iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p tcp --dport 80 -j DNAT --to-destination X.X.X.X

-> iptables -t nat -A PREROUTING -i eth0 -p tcp --dport 443 -j DNAT --to-destination X.X.X.X
